🌐 Computer Networks (Advanced System Design)
1️⃣ Design YouTube / Netflix (Core Idea 🔥)
Simple Idea

System must:

store videos
deliver videos fast
handle millions of users
Mental Model 🎬

Think of a movie distribution system:

warehouse → stores videos
delivery centers → CDN
users → viewers
High-Level Flow
User requests video
DNS finds nearest server
CDN serves video
Video streams in chunks
Why It Works
CDN reduces latency
chunking enables smooth playback
Interview Gold Line ⭐

👉 “Video systems use CDN + chunk-based streaming for scalability.”

2️⃣ Video Streaming Internals (Deep)
How Video is Sent

Video is divided into:

👉 small chunks (2–10 seconds)

Why Chunking?
avoids buffering
adapts to network speed
Adaptive Streaming

Quality changes dynamically:

slow internet → low quality
fast internet → HD
Mental Model

YouTube auto-adjusting video quality.

Memory Trick

Chunks + Adaptation = Smooth video

3️⃣ Load Balancing (Deep Level)
Simple Idea

Distribute traffic across multiple servers.

Types
Round robin
Least connections
IP hash
Mental Model 🍽️

Multiple waiters handling customers.

Why It Works
avoids overload
improves response time
Key Insight ⭐

👉 “Load balancing improves availability and performance”

4️⃣ Fault Tolerance (Very Important 🔥)
Simple Idea

System should not fail completely even if parts fail.

Mental Model 🛡️

If one road is blocked → alternate route exists.

How It Works
multiple servers
backup systems
replication
Real Example

If one YouTube server fails → another serves video.

Memory Trick

Failure ≠ system down

🌍 Social Networks (Advanced Concepts)
5️⃣ Preferential Attachment
Simple Idea

New nodes connect to already popular nodes.

Mental Model

People follow celebrities, not random users.

Why It Works
popularity attracts more popularity
Memory Trick

Rich get richer

6️⃣ Scale-Free Networks (Deep Insight)
Idea

Network has few highly connected hubs.

Example
Google
Instagram influencers
Why Important
resilient to random failures
vulnerable to targeted attacks
Memory Trick

Few hubs dominate

7️⃣ Information Diffusion Models
Simple Idea

Mathematical way to study how info spreads

Types
Independent cascade
Threshold model
Mental Model

Like disease spreading.

Why It Matters

Used in:

marketing
viral campaigns
Memory Trick

Diffusion = spreading model

8️⃣ Network Robustness (Advanced)
Simple Idea

Ability of network to survive failures.

Two Cases
random failure → network survives
targeted attack → network breaks
Mental Model

Remove random people → network ok
Remove influencers → network breaks

Memory Trick

Robust = strong against failure

